Class ParameterPreprocessingManager

    • Method Detail

      • preprocessInitialConditions

        public void preprocessInitialConditions(org.sbml.jsbml.Parameter p)
        This method pre-process a SBML Parameter in order to setup its initial conditions.
        If the Parameter is defined by an AssignmentRule, the method does nothing.
        If the Parameter is not affected by any InitialAssignment, but its field value is defined, an InitialAssignment with that value is created in the model.
        If the Parameter does not appear in any AlgebraicRule and nothing else defines its initial value, then it is assumed to be zero.
        Parameters:
        p - The SBML Parameter to analyze.

      • preprocessDerivative

        public void preprocessDerivative(org.sbml.jsbml.Parameter p)
        This method pre-process a SBML Parameter in order to setup the missing informations about its variability.
        If the Parameter is constant, then the method does nothing.
        If there exists an AssignmentRule that defines the Parameter, then the method does nothing.
        If there exists a RateRule that defines the Parameter, then the method does nothing.
        If the Parameter does not appears in any AlgebraicRule, then it is declared constant, if there is no Event that affect it, otherwise, a new RateRule with formula equals to zero is created to define the derivative of the Parameter.
        Parameters:
        p - The SBML Parameter to analyze.

      • preprocessParameters

        public void preprocessParameters()
        This method applies the pre-proecssing procedures to every Parameter in the Model.
